{"id":"277561761_Interval_Observers_for_Continuous-Time_LPV_Systems_with_L1_L2_Performance","abstract":"An approach to interval observer design for Linear Parameter-Varying (LPV) systems is proposed. It is assumed that the vector of scheduling parameters in LPV models is not available for measurement. Two different interval observers are constructed for nonnegative systems and for a generic case. Stability conditions are expressed in terms of matrix inequalities, which can be solved with respect to the observer gains using standard numerical solvers. Applying / framework the robustness and estimation accuracy with respect to model uncertainty are analyzed. The efficiency of interval estimation for LPV models is demonstrated through numerical experiments for a microfluidic system and an academic example.","authors":["Stanislav Chebotarev","Denis Efimov","Tarek Raissi","Ali Zolghadri"],"meta":["August 2015Automatica 58","DOI:10.1016/j.automatica.2015.05.009"],"references":["260586812_Stabilisation_for_a_class_of_non-linear_uncertain_systems_based_on_interval_observers","260540673_Development_of_Linear-Parameter-Varying_Models_for_Aircraft","260516633_Control_of_Nonlinear_and_LPV_Systems_Interval_Observer-Based_Framework","259829320_Fault_Detection_and_Diagnosis_in_Electrical_Aircraft_Flight_Control_System","254054386_Robust_stability_analysis_of_uncertain_linear_positive_systems_via_integral_linear_constraints_L1-_and_L-gain_characterizations","243777742_Gain-Scheduled_Missile_Autopilot_Design_using_Linear_Parameter_Varying_Transformation","241636769_L1_gain_analysis_of_linear_positive_systems_and_its_application","237063354_New_Directions_in_Nonlinear_Observer_Design","228967855_Automatic_robust_convex_programming","224367851_Tight_robust_interval_observers_An_LP_approach","220387060_Interval_State_Estimation_for_a_Class_of_Nonlinear_Systems","3335965_Parametrized_linear_matrix_inequality_techniques_in_fuzzy_control_system_design","321604070_Control_and_Observer_Desi